  "studies": [
    {
      "id": "HDP01233",
      "name": "Sensory Phenotyping to Enhance Neuropathic Pain Drug Development",
      "description": "The purpose of this study will be to collect quantitative sensory testing data from patients with neuropathic pain and use those data to develop algorithm(s) that can be used to classify patients by sensory phenotypes. We will characterize the pain phenotype and acquire data on select biological, psychological, and socio-demographic factors. This study is based on the hypothesis that the pain phenotype represents the underlying pain mechanism, thus pain treatment can be personalized by matching the drug mechanismwith the pain mechanism.",
