    {
      "id": "HDP00619",
      "name": "tDCS to decrease opioid relapse",
      "description": "Neurostimulation techniques, such as transcranial direct current stimulation (tDCS), have been used as interventions for substance use disorders. This is a supplement to the currently NIDA-funded UG3 DA047793, tDCS to Decrease Opioid Relapse, which will measure behavioral and brain responses following tDCS stimulation delivered during tasks that use a particular brain network involved in cognitive control, and utilizing FMRI to assess the effects. This supplement allows the researchers to add an EEG measurement to the study, to get a complete picture of how tDCS might affect the function of key brain networks in ways that could be helpful for SUDs.",
